Frequently Asked Question

If your question isn't addressed here, feel free to reach out—I'm always ready to provide further assistance

Ask a Question

Ask a Question

What is Onion.run?

Onion.run is a privacy-focused gateway that allows users to securely access .onion websites through a normal browser. It acts as a bridge between the surface web and Tor network, without requiring users to install special software.

Do I need Tor Browser to use Onion.run?

No. Onion.run lets you preview or fetch onion-network content securely through its own relay nodes. However, for full anonymity and access to restricted onion sites, the official Tor Browser is still recommended.

Is Onion.run illegal?

Not at all. Onion.run is a neutral gateway — it simply provides technical access to the Tor network. What users access through it determines legality. We strongly discourage using the platform for any unlawful purpose.

How does Onion.run protect my privacy?

Your requests are routed through encrypted proxy layers that prevent tracking and fingerprinting. No logs, cookies, or analytics are stored — ensuring your browsing remains private.

Can Onion.run see my data or browsing history?

No. Onion.run does not record or store identifiable data. All connections are ephemeral — they exist only during your browsing session and are automatically purged afterward.
